From 75377fc78f0acd9589a20483f2a53ca34eff405f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: korchasa <korchasa@icloud.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 10:55:52 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(engine): add `runs doctor` journal health checker with
 mechanical repair (FR-E83)

Diagnose a run's durability artifacts in three passes, reporting every
problem grouped by severity (exit 0 iff no ERRORs): journal integrity
(torn final line = WARNING, the expected crash artifact; mid-file
garbage, unknown kinds, non-monotonic seq = ERROR; duplicate event_id =
WARNING), replay invariants via the existing replayer (events after a
terminal event, undeclared nodes, unmatched attempt_completed, cost-sum
divergence), and filesystem cross-check (orphan node dirs = WARNING,
declared-but-missing dirs = ERROR, stale runs/.lock = WARNING).

--repair applies only safe mechanical fixes (torn tail: journal.jsonl.bak
backup + atomic tmp/rename rewrite; stale-lock removal) and refuses,
modifying nothing, when the run is active or the journal has errors
beyond the torn tail. --json emits the machine-readable findings list.

Doctor logic lives in src/state/doctor.ts (thin CLI wiring per the
FR-E75 command-layer pattern); RunJournalEventKind is now derived from
the runtime RUN_JOURNAL_EVENT_KINDS const; lock.ts exports
isProcessAlive so lock-PID knowledge stays in one module.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
