+# engine: `runs doctor` — journal health checker with mechanical repair
+
+## Goal
+
+Give operators one CLI command that diagnoses a run's durability artifacts
+(`journal.jsonl`, node directories, `runs/.lock`) and applies only safe
+mechanical repairs (torn final journal line, stale lock), so degraded runs
+can be inspected and recovered without hand-editing the journal.
+
+## Overview
+
+### Context
+
+A run's only durable record is its append-only `journal.jsonl` (FR-E69),
+replayed via `src/state/run-journal.ts::replayRunJournal` to reconstruct
+`RunState`. Crashes, manual tampering, and engine bugs can degrade the
+journal or the surrounding run directory. Today the only tolerance is
+implicit: the replayer ignores a torn final line and dedupes duplicate
+`event_id`s; everything else throws on first error. There is no tool that
+reports EVERY problem, cross-checks the filesystem, or repairs the known
+crash artifact.
+
+### Current State
+
+- `src/state/run-journal.ts` — single source of replay truth.
+  `parseJournal` tolerates a partial tail (no trailing newline) and throws
+  on mid-file garbage; `replayRunJournal` dedupes `event_id`s and applies
+  events (terminal events dominate). Unknown `kind`s are silently ignored
+  by the replay switch.
+- `src/state/lock.ts` — `defaultLockPath(workflowDir)` =
+  `<workflowDir>/runs/.lock`; `readLockInfo`, `isRunLive` (lock names run
+  + PID alive). PID liveness check (`isProcessAlive`) is module-private.
+- `src/state/state.ts` — `getRunDir(runId, workflowDir)` =
+  `<workflowDir>/runs/<runId>`; node dirs may be phase-nested
+  (`<runDir>/<phase>/<nodeId>`).
+- `src/engine/engine.ts::emitBootstrapJournal` declares every node
+  (`node_declared`) and every node dir (`node_directory_declared`, with
+  workDir-relative `node_dir`); `createRunDirs` eagerly mkdirs all node
+  dirs at bootstrap — so a declared-but-missing dir is tampering, not a
+  normal crash artifact.
+- `src/cli.ts` — manual `for`-loop argument parsing (see
+  `parseAnswerArgs`); subcommand dispatch in `import.meta.main`; CLI is a
+  thin layer over command modules (FR-E75 pattern).
+- `types.ts` — `RunJournalEventKind` is a type-only union (no runtime
+  list of valid kinds).
+
+### Constraints
+
+- Existing replayer is the single source of replay truth — doctor only
+  orchestrates and inspects `replayRunJournal`'s result. A line-level
+  lexical integrity scan (JSON-parse per line, seq/event_id/kind checks)
+  is NOT a second replayer — it reconstructs no state.
+- Reuse `getRunDir`/`getJournalPath`/`defaultLockPath`/`readLockInfo`/
+  `isRunLive`; no duplicated path or lock knowledge. Export the existing
+  `isProcessAlive` from `lock.ts` instead of re-implementing it.
+- Follow `src/cli.ts` argument-parsing style; no new dependencies.
+- `--repair` applies ONLY mechanical fixes; refusals modify nothing.
+- `deno task check` stays green; FR-E83 registered in
+  `documents/requirements-engine/01-execution-model.md` (durability/
+  recovery area) per SRS conventions (`**Description:**`/`**Acceptance
+  criteria:**` with Tests, as used by neighboring sections).
+- Out of scope: journal compaction, multi-run batch, interactive prompts.
+
+### Severity & decision log (recorded for review)
+
+- Torn final line (last line, no trailing newline) → WARNING — the
+  expected crash artifact the writer already tolerates. A garbage final
+  line WITH trailing newline is an ERROR (matches replayer, which throws).
+- Mid-file garbage line → ERROR. Unknown event `kind` → ERROR.
+  Non-monotonic `seq` → ERROR (writer bug; replayer does not dedupe it).
+  Duplicate `event_id` → WARNING (replayer dedupes).
+- Events after terminal run event, undeclared-node lifecycle events,
+  `attempt_completed` without matching `attempt_started` (keyed by
+  `node_id` + `iteration`), cost-sum divergence → ERROR each.
+- Cost divergence semantics: the replayed `total_cost_usd` derives from
+  node snapshots (`event.node.cost_usd`) and is recomputed by
+  `updateRunCost`, so it always equals the snapshot sum by construction.
+  The independent per-node evidence is the top-level `cost_usd` metadata
+  on node lifecycle events (the writer mirrors it from `metadata`).
+  Doctor compares replayed `state.total_cost_usd` against the sum of the
+  latest per-node top-level `cost_usd`; drift = engine bug or tampering.
+  Epsilon 1e-9.
+- Orphan node dir (on disk, no journal mention) → WARNING (junk does not
+  compromise replay). Declared dir missing on disk → ERROR (the journal
+  promises artifacts that are gone; engine mkdirs all node dirs eagerly,
+  so absence is not a crash artifact). Known infra entries at run root
+  are exempt from orphan detection: `logs`, `worktree`, `.hitl-inbox`,
+  plus non-directories.
+- Stale `runs/.lock` referencing this run with dead PID → WARNING. Lock
+  referencing a different run, or corrupt lock → not this run's finding;
+  ignored.
+- Missing journal file → ERROR (no further journal/filesystem checks; the
+  lock check still runs). Replay throw (mixed run, event before
+  `run_started`, mid-file garbage) → ERROR `REPLAY_FAILED`; replay-
+  invariant and filesystem checks are skipped since there is no trusted
+  event list.
+- Exit code: 0 when zero ERRORs, 1 otherwise (`--repair` refusal exits 1).
+  Argument errors print `Error: …` and exit 1 (mirrors `runAnswer`).
+- Repair refusal conditions checked BEFORE any modification: (a) the run
+  is currently active (`isRunLive`); (b) journal has ERRORs beyond the
+  torn final line (any journal-integrity or replay ERROR). Filesystem
+  findings (orphan/missing dir) do not block mechanical repairs.
+- `--repair` with nothing repairable is a no-op success (reported).
+
