+## Solution
+
+### Selected Variant
+
+V2 — dedicated `src/state/doctor.ts` command module + thin CLI wiring
+(see Variant Analysis in the session log; rationale: matches the FR-E75
+thin-CLI/command-layer architecture, unit-testable without spawning the
+CLI, reuses all existing state helpers, no speculative abstraction).
+
+### Files to create / modify
+
+- `src/types.ts` — introduce runtime list
+  `RUN_JOURNAL_EVENT_KINDS` (`as const`) and derive
+  `RunJournalEventKind = (typeof RUN_JOURNAL_EVENT_KINDS)[number]`
+  (type stays identical; gives doctor a runtime kind whitelist).
+- `src/state/lock.ts` — export existing `isProcessAlive` (reuse, no
+  duplication).
+- New `src/state/doctor.ts`:
+  - `DoctorFinding { severity: "error" | "warning"; code: string;
+    message: string; path?: string }`.
+  - `DoctorRepair { code: string; message: string; path: string }`.
+  - `DoctorReport { run_id, workflow_dir, findings, repairs,
+    errors, warnings, ok }` (`ok` = zero errors).
+  - `diagnoseRun({ workflowDir, runId })` — pipeline:
+    1. Journal integrity: read `getJournalPath(getRunDir(...))`; line
+       scan (JSON.parse per line; torn-tail detection identical to the
+       replayer's rule: last line + no trailing newline; valid byte
+       prefix recorded for repair); kind whitelist; seq monotonicity
+       (skipping duplicate `event_id` lines); duplicate `event_id`s.
+    2. Replay invariants: call `replayRunJournal` (the existing
+       replayer) in try/catch; on throw → `REPLAY_FAILED` ERROR and
+       skip 2/3. From `replay.events` (deduped): events after first
+       terminal event; lifecycle events for undeclared nodes;
+       `attempt_completed` without prior unconsumed `attempt_started`
+       (key `node_id`/`iteration`); cost-sum divergence per decision
+       log.
+    3. Filesystem cross-check: declared run-relative node dirs from
+       `node_directory_declared` (`node_dir` suffix after
+       `runs/<runId>/`); orphans on disk (depth 1, phase dirs
+       descended one level, infra entries exempt); declared-but-missing
+       dirs; stale-lock check via `readLockInfo` +
+       `isProcessAlive`.
+  - `repairRun(...)` — refusal checks first (live lock via `isRunLive`;
+    journal/replay ERRORs beyond torn tail), then: torn tail → copy
+    `journal.jsonl` → `journal.jsonl.bak`, write valid prefix to
+    `journal.jsonl.tmp`, `Deno.rename` over original; stale lock →
+    `Deno.remove(defaultLockPath(workflowDir))`.
+  - `doctorRun({ workflowDir, runId, repair })` — orchestrates diagnose
+    (+ optional repair + re-diagnose after repair so the report reflects
+    the healed state), returns `DoctorReport`.
+  - `formatDoctorReport(report)` — human-readable report grouped
+    ERROR / WARNING / OK summary.
+  - Finding codes: `JOURNAL_MISSING`, `JOURNAL_TORN_TAIL`,
+    `JOURNAL_GARBAGE_LINE`, `JOURNAL_UNKNOWN_KIND`,
+    `JOURNAL_NON_MONOTONIC_SEQ`, `JOURNAL_DUPLICATE_EVENT_ID`,
+    `REPLAY_FAILED`, `EVENT_AFTER_TERMINAL`, `NODE_NOT_DECLARED`,
+    `ATTEMPT_WITHOUT_START`, `COST_SUM_DIVERGENCE`, `ORPHAN_NODE_DIR`,
+    `MISSING_DECLARED_DIR`, `STALE_LOCK`; repair codes
+    `REPAIR_TORN_TAIL`, `REPAIR_STALE_LOCK`; refusal code
+    `REPAIR_REFUSED` (error severity).
